<rss version="2.0" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:ss="http://contenthub.aol.com/slideshow/"><channel><title><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></title><link/> https://www.engadget.com/ <description><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></description><language>英文</language><copyright>版权所有雅虎 2023</copyright><pubDate> Wed, 21 Jun 2023 15:15:28 +0000</pubDate><generator>雅虎 http://yahoo.com </generator><item><title><![CDATA[FTC sues Amazon for allegedly tricking customers into Prime subscriptions]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>尽管<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-settles-lawsuit-with-ftc-over-ring-doorbell-privacy-concerns-191257621.html">最近有两项</a><a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-will-pay-25-million-to-settle-ftc-lawsuit-over-alexa-privacy-for-kids-193330840.html">和解</a>，但联邦贸易委员会 (FTC) 对亚马逊的处理仍未结束。该机构<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/news/press-releases/2023/06/ftc-takes-action-against-amazon-enrolling-consumers-amazon-prime-without-consent-sabotaging-their">已起诉</a>亚马逊，指控该公司欺骗客户注册 Prime，同时阻止取消的企图。据称，这家在线零售商通过误导性设计让用户在未经真正同意的情况下注册 Prime，从而违反了 FTC 法案和恢复在线购物者信心法案。 FTC 认为，领导者甚至“放慢或拒绝”设计变更，这些变更本可以更容易取消 Prime。</p><p>我们已征求亚马逊的意见。 FTC 主席 Lina Khan 在一份声明中坚称，亚马逊“欺骗和困住了”客户。她说，这既激怒了用户，又让他们损失了“大笔金钱”。 FTC 还声称，亚马逊曾多次试图“拖延和阻碍”调查。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>正如<em>CNBC</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.cnbc.com/2023/06/21/ftc-sues-amazon-over-deceptive-prime-sign-up-and-cancellation-process.html">指出的</a>那样，美国联邦贸易委员会自 2021 年 3 月以来一直在调查亚马逊 Prime 注册和取消系统。在<em>Insider</em>表示其<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.businessinsider.com/amazon-prime-ftc-probe-customer-complaints-sign-ups-internal-documents-2022-3">获得的</a>内部文件据称显示亚马逊早在 2017 年就知道客户反对意见后，调查在 2022 年加深了。在结账时单击一下即可注册 30 天试用，但在试用结束前必须费力浏览多个页面才能取消服务。亚马逊甚至使用“伊利亚特”一词来描述取消过程，暗指荷马史诗的绝对长度。</p><p>可汗领导下的联邦贸易委员会密切审查了亚马逊的做法。官员们已经审查了这家互联网巨头<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ftc-amazon-mgm-investigation-195722033.html">对 MGM</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-completes-one-medical-acquisition-163431975.html">One Medical</a>的收购，以及 Alexa 和 Ring 门铃的隐私问题。在被提名为 FTC 主席之前，Khan 是 Big Tech 的著名批评者，亚马逊甚至<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-ftc-chair-lina-khan-recusal-antitrust-investigations-181556108.html">要求她在反垄断案件中回避</a>声称的偏见。</p><p>欺骗性设计的概念，也称为“ <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-01-13-websites-not-following-eu-gdpr-rules-study.html">黑暗模式</a>”，并不新鲜。 2020 年，欧盟表示，许多网站让拒绝跟踪 cookie 变得不必要地困难。然而，针对亚马逊的诉讼是对这些模式在美国合法性的重大考验。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/ftc-sues-amazon-for-allegedly-tricking-customers-into-prime-subscriptions-151528914.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/ftc-sues-amazon-for-allegedly-tricking-customers-into-prime-subscriptions-151528914.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 476e92f0-436f-4845-8909-dfae899e9653</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 21 Jun 2023 15:15:28 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687360056</ingested><modified> 2023-06-21T15:07:41+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="2153" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-07/316bb6b0-e54c-11eb-af34-55c9c115b936" w